1
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:21,632
There is no God!

2
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,391
Forgive me.

3
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,514
Give me a sign.

4
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,558
Help me.

5
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:52,235
Maureen. Maureen, where are you, dear?.

6
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,870
Maureen, where are you?.

7
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:57,430
Oh dear God. She's up there.

8
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,558
Maureen!

9
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:01,871
Stay where you are!

10
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,918
Don't move!

11
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:09,269
Stay where you are.
- Come down!

12
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,555
There is no God!

13
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:16,599
Wretched girl, how dare you!
- Get away from me!

14
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,831
Please, Maureen. You mustn't.

15
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:23,074
You have an obligation to Him.
- I have nothing.

16
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:27,917
I am nothing.
- You can't. - No!

17
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:42,076
Wasn't your own sin red enough?.
You'll burn in hell for this!

18
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,789
You'll burn in hell!

19
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,399
Maureen!

20
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:44,354
Want a ride?. Or do you have
the Olympic torch in the suitcase?.

21
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,755
Wouldn't want to lose ya.

22
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,999
Don't worry.
I ain't born again or nothing.

23
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:57,597
I'll get this junk out of your way.

24
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,389
Jesus just come with it
when I bought her used.

25
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:04,554
I wanted to replace it
with a magnetic compass,

26
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,554
but you usually end up
going the wrong direction anyway.

27
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:10,599
That makes two of us.
- Yeah?.

28
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,394
Water?.
- Thank you.

29
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:21,912
Name's Duane Duke, by the way.
Friends just call me Duke.

30
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:29,716
Put the suitcase in the back seat.
- Thank you.

31
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,151
Hey, watch the guitar!
- I'm sorry.

32
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:37,838
No harm done.
Just watch out. It's my life.

33
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:42,677
Going to LAA to be a rock-n-roll star.
What about you?. Where you going?.

34
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:46,117
What were you doing back there?.
- l...

35
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:50,399
Car trouble?.
- Yes. I had car trouble.

36
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,233
What kind?.

37
00:04:54,520 --> 00:05:00,390
AAh, no car.
- No car?. That's the worst kind.

38
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,997
Still don't know where you come from.
- So?.

39
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:08,279
AAre you my Father confessor?.
- Jesus,

40
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:12,958
I was just asking! You act as if
I accused you of murder or something.

41
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:17,712
Hey, it's none of my business.
Play mystery lady if you want.

42
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:22,591
I don't care where you come from.
Could've fallen from the sky.

43
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,878
AA little angel
just tumbled off her cloud.

44
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:30,478
Well, hold on angel,
I'll get you where you're going.

45
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,797
Get out of here!

46
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,791
Come on, baby.

47
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,150
You alright?.
- Yes.

48
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:32,192
What are you doing?. - It's as
far as we go in this shit, honey.

49
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,434
But it could rain all night.
- That's right.

50
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,511
Better get some sleep.

51
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,677
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

52
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,429
You kind of slid over.

53
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,956
It's still raining.

54
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,671
Why did you do that?.
- Why didn't you stop me?.

55
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:52,470
I didn't have time.
- I'll give you another chance.

56
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:58,076
I'm not very good at this.
- You could have fooled me.

57
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,318
Please don't!

58
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:09,317
Oh, well, I guess
we got him a little excited.

59
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,869
Don't!

60
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,795
No!

61
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,719
What's the problem, angel?.

62
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,636
Get away from me!

63
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:31,431
AAre you crazy?. Get in here!
- Give me my suitcase.

64
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:37,669
Stupid bitch!

65
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,197
You could've been coming
instead of going.

66
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:21,236
AAre you really my mother?.
- The name Spool means nothing to you?.

67
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:25,076
No. Should it?.
- It was Norma Bates' maiden name.

68
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,835
The woman you thought was
your mother was my sister.

69
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:31,516
She never mentioned me, did she?.
- No.

70
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:34,275
You sure you won't have a sandwich?.

71
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,118
Pardon?.

72
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,674
Hi there.

73
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,397
Be right down.

74
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,275
Room?.

75
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:30,319
I'd love one,
but I don't think I can afford it.

76
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,632
You should keep the register closed.
Somebody'll steal you blind.

77
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:36,793
Wouldn't get them very far.
- Business slow?.

78
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:41,830
You're my first customer of the day.
Or did you just need directions?.

79
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:46,153
I was actually interested in the sign.
But if business is bad...

80
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:50,075
No, it's not bad, just slow.

81
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,914
Well, 12 cabins, 12 vacancies...
We've been closed for a while.

82
00:13:57,320 --> 00:14:00,153
Renovations.
But life's picking up along here.

83
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,391
Good prices, good service.
Things'll pick up.

84
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:06,236
I've got a rebuilt ice machine,
and 4 cabins booked for this week.

85
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:10,350
Fairvale High's Homecoming.
Big game against Central.

86
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:14,551
I'm rattling on.
Yes, there is a job. Interested?.

87
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:19,033
In money?. The only honest way
to get it is to earn it or inherit it.

88
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:22,830
AAnd I don't have any rich relatives.
Got an application form?.

89
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:25,674
Not necessary. My name is Norman,

90
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,957
Norman Bates.

91
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,233
What'ya been painting?.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

92
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:37,191
Step into the back while I clean up.
- Said the spider to the fly.

93
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:47,313
Local branch of the AAudubon society?.
- My hobby. Stuffing things.

94
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:51,838
Have a seat...
- Duane Duke. Just call me Duke.

95
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,396
I can pay you 5 dollars an hour.

96
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:58,395
You'd work the desk,
make beds, clean up. Stuff like that.

97
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:04,310
Want some of these?.
You'd be general assistant.

98
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:08,190
Work's not too hard,
and you'd have lots of free time.

99
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:12,754
I'm the manager,
so you'd be assistant manager.

100
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:17,756
You'd get a free room and work days.
I prefer the nights.

101
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,116
I've got to be honest, Norm.
- Norman.

102
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:23,956
I just want to make enough bucks
to get my car fixed and

103
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:27,591
build up a little stake for LAA.
I'm a singer.

104
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:33,119
But I could fill in until you found
somebody permanent. I'm just not

105
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,999
staying too long.

106
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,673
No one ever does.

107
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:43,713
Your cabin's at the end.
Why don't you go unpack?.

108
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:46,953
I need to get back to the house.

109
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,999
You live up there?.
- Yeah.

110
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,591
Me and myself, alone.

111
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:03,874
You clear on the credit card machine?.
- Yeah, I used to be a pump jockey.

112
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:08,239
The rooms cost...
- 20.95 single, 25.95 double.

113
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:11,837
I'll bring you a couple of burgers.
- AAlright!

114
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:20,718
Still beats the hell out of me.
Just doesn't show up for work one day.

115
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:24,835
Thought you would've turned up
some clues by now, John.

116
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:30,234
Her apartment's all in order.
Didn't say anything to her landlord.

117
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:34,553
You'd think she'd tell me
if she was going to take a month off.

118
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,837
Emma Spool
was as regular as clockwork.

119
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:40,550
I don't think she missed a day
in the 7 years I've owned this dump.

120
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:45,750
I hope that nothing's happened to her.
- You mean like Norman Bates?.

121
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:51,470
Didn't they work here together?.
They say he likes older women.

122
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:55,675
Rumors and innuendo caused
that boy enough trouble.

123
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:59,390
What's your interest anyway?.
- I drove from LAA to see him.

124
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:02,792
Why?. You another relative
of somebody he killed?.

125
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:05,555
It's really not any of your business.

126
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,712
Keeping the peace is my business.

127
00:17:08,120 --> 00:17:11,271
Then until I've broken some law,
lay off the third-degree, OK?.

128
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,148
Can't you just leave
the poor slob alone?.

129
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:19,588
What are you?. His fan club?.
- No, we believe in second chances.

130
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,992
What Norman did was a long time ago,
and he paid the price.

131
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:25,311
It depends on who you ask.

132
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:28,598
20 years in the bunk house
is paying the price, girly.

133
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,558
The guy's okay now.

134
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:34,032
When he worked here,
he was always on time and reliable.

135
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:36,556
AA real Employee of the Month!

136
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:42,354
Go ahead and talk smart, lady.
He just wants to be left in peace.

137
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:48,949
Now look, Norman Bates has suffered
enough. Just leave him...

138
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:52,356
AAfternoon, sheriff.
-... alone.

139
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,320
Mrs. Dudley...
- What'll it be, Norman?.

140
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,789
Chicken fried steak is good today.

141
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:03,239
AAlright, and a glass of milk, please.
AAnd a couple of burgers to go.

142
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:05,915
I'm warning you. I don't want trouble.

143
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:10,393
Then let go of my arm
or I'll holler police brutality.

144
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:16,477
Mind if I join you, Mr. Bates?.
Tracy Vanderbilt.

145
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:20,592
Thanks, Myrna.

146
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,235
Coastal Reports?.
- I write for them sometimes.

147
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:27,871
If you don't mind, I'd like to ask you
a few questions. - I mind.

148
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:31,750
Mr. Bates... - Norman.
- I'm writing on the insanity defense

149
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:34,799
and the rehabilitation
of mentally ill murderers.

150
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:39,113
Many people think
they can't be rehabilitated

151
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,715
and there shouldn't be
an insanity defense.

152
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:47,114
We hear the objections of the victims
and relatives, but the murderers,

153
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:52,878
who can't help themselves,
are victims too. What do you think?.

154
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:55,999
If this lady's bothering you,
I'll have her leave.

155
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:58,995
Isn't your coffee break over, sheriff?.

156
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,956
AAnything else, Norman?.

157
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,836
What do you think?.
- AAbout?. - What we were just saying.

158
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:14,392
You were incarcerated for 20 years.
- 22.

159
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:18,549
Right.
For 22 years, you were locked away.

160
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:21,394
The state says you're sane.
You paid your debt.

161
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,917
Then Lila Loomis starts
to persecute you. - Because of

162
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,197
what happened to her sister.
- Yes.

163
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,716
Marion Crane. Right?.

164
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:40,557
Right.
- But that was 20 years ago.

165
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,279
22.

166
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,353
AA long time to harbor revenge.

167
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:49,833
AAren't you bitter about
what Lila Loomis tried to do to you?.

168
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,274
I understand.

169
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:55,148
My cure
couldn't cure the hurt I caused.

170
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:58,711
My return to sanity
didn't return the dead.

171
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:01,076
There's no way
to make up that loss.

172
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:04,153
The past is never really past.

173
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:08,109
It stays with me all the time.
No matter how hard I try,

174
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:12,877
I can't escape. It's always there.
Throbbing inside you.

175
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:17,432
Coloring your perceptions of the world,
and sometimes controlling them.

176
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,671
That's my point, Norman. You have

177
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:22,833
a conscience. You live with guilt.
You punish yourself all the time.

178
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,996
Why does the rest of society have to?.

179
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:29,995
Take Mrs. Spool's disappearance.
What if a well-meaning citizen

180
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:32,834
thought that
you had something to do with it?.

181
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,793
I'm not upsetting you, Norman?.
AAll this talk

182
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,475
is only hypothetical.
- What's yours, babe?.

183
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:49,190
She is only an example
of how people might,

184
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,431
given your past history,

185
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:56,357
tend to automatically blame you
for any murder in the area.

186
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:19,432
You're not going, Norman?.
I'd like to talk to you again.

187
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:24,033
You're not going to stiff us, Norman?.

188
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:30,196
Excuse me. Could you tell me,
is there a cheap place to stay here?.

189
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:49,508
Hello, angel.

190
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,353
You work here?.

191
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:55,479
It's called suffering for one's art.
I'm sorry about last night.

192
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:58,519
I was a little road-weary.
I'm glad you didn't drown.

193
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,239
I'm so very tired.

194
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:03,438
You won't find another place close.

195
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:09,560
Don't worry. AAside from total boredom,
nothing will happen to you here.

196
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,397
Maureen Coil. Pretty name.

197
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:29,754
How much?.
- For a single, $25.95.

198
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:44,509
There you go, angel.
Enjoy your stay.

199
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:12,748
Your type, Norm?.
- You gave her Cabin 1.

200
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,829
Makes it kind of cosy.

201
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:19,949
Clean her up a little,
she'll look pretty good.

202
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:38,399
Put me closer to the window.
- Someone will see you, Mother.

203
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:40,995
AAre you ashamed of me?.

204
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:44,756
You know why, Mother. They've
even written about you in the paper.

205
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:48,948
Stop your whining, boy.
AAll this fuss over nothing.

206
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:52,115
Not nothing. I saw her.

207
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:57,036
Even the initials on the suitcase.
M.C., Marion Crane.

208
00:24:57,440 --> 00:25:02,275
AAnother of your cheap,
erotic delusions.

209
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,309
You killed her.
The slut deserved it. But she's dead.

210
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,756
AAnd the dead don't come back.

211
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:12,799
You came back.
- I never went away.

212
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:17,716
Don't you know that by now?.
You can't get rid of me.

213
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,630
I'll always be with you, Norman.

214
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:22,799
AAlways.

215
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,119
Stand up straight and
wipe your snotty little nose.

216
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:31,753
If the disgusting little whore upsets
you so much, just get rid of her.

217
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,115
No!

218
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,839
Then maybe I will.

219
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:04,953
You have an obligation, Maureen.
Maureen, don't!

220
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:07,430
There is no God.

221
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:12,914
Please Maureen, you mustn't.
Get away. You'll burn in hell.

222
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:17,154
You have an obligation.
I have nothing.

223
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:20,358
I am nothing.

224
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:48,239
What'll it be?.
- Give me a beer.

225
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,155
Hi.

226
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:06,394
I'm Duane.
- No kidding?.

227
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:13,397
AAny objections
to a guy buying you a drink?.

228
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:17,270
I got a drink.
- So have another.

229
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:20,353
You got a limit?.
- Only to my patience.

230
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:24,309
You don't have to call me Duane.
- No, I don't. - Friends call me Duke.

231
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:26,597
I had a dog named Duke once.
- Really?.

232
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:31,437
Scratch my belly, my leg'll shake.
- I hated the mutt.

233
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:39,476
Keep the matches, lady. You need 'em.
You're as warm as a cry for help.

234
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:44,119
Just a minute. Duke. AAh, Duane.

235
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:48,392
Whatever. I'm easy.
- I've noticed.

236
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,109
You staying there?.
