492
01:01:55,280 --> 01:01:56,998
Come on, Leo.

493
01:01:58,920 --> 01:02:01,992
Don't go up there.
- Why?. Something's wrong with Norman?.

494
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:05,392
It's time somebody told you.

495
01:02:27,200 --> 01:02:31,512
Good morning, Norman. It's a bit hot
to be sleeping so late, isn't it?.

496
01:02:31,920 --> 01:02:33,956
We had a lot of revelers last night.
- I know.

497
01:02:34,360 --> 01:02:37,909
One didn't come home.
Name is Patsy Boyle.

498
01:02:38,320 --> 01:02:41,949
She came with a group of locals
to party after the game.

499
01:02:42,880 --> 01:02:46,998
When they all left around 3,
nobody noticed that she wasn't there.

500
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:51,632
Someone's missing and you come to me.
- There have been other accusations.

501
01:02:52,040 --> 01:02:54,235
From that reporter! She knows nothing.

502
01:02:54,640 --> 01:02:58,315
That's what we're going to find out.
Now it's too hot to argue.

503
01:02:58,720 --> 01:03:02,395
That rain made everything more muggy.
- Nothing back there. - Of course not.

504
01:03:02,800 --> 01:03:04,995
Please get out of my house.
- Sorry, Norman.

505
01:03:05,400 --> 01:03:10,269
We have the warrant.
It's in everybody's best interest.

506
01:03:11,280 --> 01:03:13,589
Who's?. There's nothing here.
I didn't do anything.

507
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:18,152
Then there's nothing to worry about.
Norman, come back!

508
01:03:19,680 --> 01:03:22,240
Get him, Leo. Doggone you!

509
01:03:45,120 --> 01:03:48,829
Norman,
what the hell's the matter with you?.

510
01:03:54,560 --> 01:03:55,959
Mother?.

511
01:04:00,680 --> 01:04:02,193
I'm sorry, Norman.

512
01:04:03,240 --> 01:04:06,676
AAll seems a little unnecessary now.
- That's okay.

513
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:10,959
Still no reason to get so...
so riled up.

514
01:04:11,360 --> 01:04:13,590
We'll leave you alone now. AAgain,

515
01:04:14,000 --> 01:04:17,072
I'm sorry. - That's not enough.
You just can't let it lie!

516
01:04:17,480 --> 01:04:20,916
I've had enough
of this Nancy Drew horseshit.

517
01:04:21,920 --> 01:04:24,229
I'm letting it lie and so are you.

518
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:29,948
Until I have evidence to the contrary,
both ladies are missing persons.

519
01:04:30,360 --> 01:04:32,237
AAren't you going to question him?.

520
01:04:32,640 --> 01:04:35,916
Why not drag the swamp?.
He dumped the last bodies there.

521
01:04:36,320 --> 01:04:38,709
Don't tell me my job,
Ms. Vanderbilt.

522
01:04:39,120 --> 01:04:41,236
Somebody has to.

523
01:04:41,640 --> 01:04:45,872
You're not going to let him go?.
- Despite all your glib insinuations,

524
01:04:46,280 --> 01:04:49,431
I don't have one iota of proof.
- He didn't do it.

525
01:04:49,840 --> 01:04:52,434
Norman was with me
until 6 o'clock this morning.

526
01:04:52,840 --> 01:04:54,990
Whatever happened to that girl,

527
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:58,437
he didn't have anything to do with it.
- Well, Miss,

528
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:04,189
had you told us sooner, you would
have saved us a lot of trouble.

529
01:05:04,600 --> 01:05:07,478
No one asked me.
- Come on, Leo.

530
01:05:08,240 --> 01:05:10,595
Bad time to beat the street, Norman.

531
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:13,833
You'd better follow
the sheriff's example.

532
01:05:14,240 --> 01:05:19,598
I'm taking a passenger. Ready?.

533
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:33,193
She told you about me, didn't she?.
- Yes.

534
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:35,397
Where are you going?.

535
01:05:36,960 --> 01:05:40,589
Father Brian said I could come stay
with him if I needed to.

536
01:05:41,000 --> 01:05:43,070
Please let me go.

537
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:15,194
Mother!

538
01:06:18,640 --> 01:06:19,789
Mother!

539
01:06:45,800 --> 01:06:47,995
Mother, where are you?.

540
01:07:50,320 --> 01:07:53,790
I love the silver
that shines in your hair.

541
01:07:54,200 --> 01:07:58,159
AAnd the brow that's all furled
and wrinkled with care.

542
01:07:58,560 --> 01:08:02,348
I kissed the dear fingers,
so toilworn for me.

543
01:08:02,760 --> 01:08:07,515
Oh God bless you and keep you,
dear Mother...

544
01:08:08,520 --> 01:08:09,589
Bates.

545
01:08:12,200 --> 01:08:15,112
It doesn't scan, does it, Norman?.

546
01:08:15,960 --> 01:08:16,995
But...

547
01:08:17,400 --> 01:08:20,073
a lot of shit around here doesn't.

548
01:08:20,480 --> 01:08:22,232
What are you doing with my mother?.

549
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:24,433
Don't you mean...

550
01:08:24,840 --> 01:08:26,353
Mummy?.

551
01:08:29,720 --> 01:08:32,188
You did a nice job on her, Norman.

552
01:08:32,600 --> 01:08:34,795
Fresh as the day she was croaked.

553
01:08:38,040 --> 01:08:38,950
Why?.

554
01:08:39,360 --> 01:08:41,032
Just looking out for you.

555
01:08:41,440 --> 01:08:44,512
AAnd yourself.
- I have ambitions, dreams.

556
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:47,480
But dreams don't come cheap nowadays.

557
01:08:47,880 --> 01:08:50,235
I could have turned
Mom over to the cops,

558
01:08:50,640 --> 01:08:53,950
but all I would have gotten
was a pat on the back.

559
01:08:55,080 --> 01:08:57,594
That reporter
would've shelled out a few bucks,

560
01:08:58,000 --> 01:09:02,596
and gotten the lion's share
of the credit, a five-figure salary,

561
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:05,195
and a big news job.

562
01:09:05,600 --> 01:09:09,752
Fine for her dreams,
but what about mine?. No.

563
01:09:10,160 --> 01:09:14,950
I figure Mama's greatest value to me
is in her value to you.

564
01:09:15,360 --> 01:09:17,669
I don't have that kind of money.
- Don't gripe to me.

565
01:09:18,080 --> 01:09:20,878
With that big piece of real estate
and this thriving business,

566
01:09:21,280 --> 01:09:24,875
you could just sell an acre.

567
01:09:25,480 --> 01:09:28,040
Please, Duke.
I want my mother back.

568
01:09:28,440 --> 01:09:31,671
Take her. You know what I want.

569
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:35,478
AAnd you know what I'll do
if I don't get it.

570
01:09:35,880 --> 01:09:37,757
I know.

571
01:09:43,040 --> 01:09:46,032
I'm going to kill you,
you little freak.

572
01:10:01,680 --> 01:10:03,716
You think I'm stupid, Duke?.

573
01:10:05,120 --> 01:10:09,159
Even if I gave you money,
you'd still tell on Mother.

574
01:10:09,560 --> 01:10:12,120
No one must know what she did.

575
01:10:15,680 --> 01:10:17,352
She can't help it.

576
01:10:17,760 --> 01:10:22,197
She can't help the things she does.
She's just an old lady.

577
01:10:22,600 --> 01:10:24,192
AA sick, old lady.

578
01:10:33,400 --> 01:10:34,958
Watch the guitar!

579
01:10:44,880 --> 01:10:48,919
You shouldn't sneak up
on a guy like that, Duke. Duke?.

580
01:10:50,120 --> 01:10:53,396
I didn't mean it.

581
01:10:55,880 --> 01:10:59,668
You made me do this!
Your tainted blood in me!

582
01:11:01,920 --> 01:11:06,152
Don't laugh at me, Mother.
Don't laugh at me.

583
01:11:08,960 --> 01:11:13,715
I didn't even know she had any kids.
- Wasn't it on her job application?.

584
01:11:14,120 --> 01:11:16,680
She was already here
when I bought the place 7 years ago.

585
01:11:17,080 --> 01:11:21,312
Best waitress I ever had.
- She worked for the previous owner?.

586
01:11:21,720 --> 01:11:25,190
Harvey Leech. - Where's he now?.
- He used to be in a nursing home.

587
01:11:25,600 --> 01:11:28,797
Outside town.
- Probably dead now.

588
01:11:35,080 --> 01:11:37,719
Spool?.
- Emma Spool.

589
01:11:38,120 --> 01:11:41,510
She worked in your diner.
- Diner?.

590
01:11:42,280 --> 01:11:46,512
Yeah, I had a diner once.
- Mrs. Spool used to work for you.

591
01:11:46,920 --> 01:11:51,391
I had a woman named Spool
who used to work for me. AA waitress.

592
01:11:51,800 --> 01:11:53,711
She come from that place.
- Place?.

593
01:11:54,120 --> 01:11:57,669
That place for nuts. AAs-s-asylum.

594
01:11:58,080 --> 01:12:00,275
Mrs Spool was in an asylum?.

595
01:12:00,680 --> 01:12:03,797
AAsylum, that's it, asylum.

596
01:12:04,200 --> 01:12:06,668
You know, she killed somebody.

597
01:12:07,480 --> 01:12:10,358
Who?.
- Somebody. Husband?.

598
01:12:13,400 --> 01:12:18,269
I don't recall. Good waitress, Spool.

599
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:24,789
AAre you sure, Maureen?.
- Oh yes.

600
01:12:25,200 --> 01:12:28,237
Norman understands me.
He understands forgiveness.

601
01:12:28,640 --> 01:12:32,235
I failed so many people, Father.
I won't fail him.

602
01:12:32,640 --> 01:12:36,918
That's why Mary came to me
the night he saved my life.

603
01:12:37,320 --> 01:12:39,470
It was a sign.

604
01:12:41,360 --> 01:12:46,115
AAnd the woman in the window.
That must've been Mary too.

605
01:13:20,560 --> 01:13:22,357
I'll be back, Mother.

606
01:15:29,800 --> 01:15:34,032
Miserere mei, Deus...

607
01:16:47,200 --> 01:16:51,591
I thought if she saw these copies
she might change her story.

608
01:16:53,520 --> 01:16:55,351
Can I see her?.

609
01:16:55,760 --> 01:16:57,398
I'm afraid not.

610
01:17:20,760 --> 01:17:21,829
Norman!

611
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:53,798
Norman?. It's me.

612
01:17:55,560 --> 01:17:57,710
I've come back.

613
01:18:04,560 --> 01:18:07,358
I never should've gone away.

614
01:18:09,200 --> 01:18:12,670
Whatever happened to you in your past,

615
01:18:13,080 --> 01:18:16,231
I know you're good. You took a life,

616
01:18:16,640 --> 01:18:19,074
but you also saved a life.

617
01:18:19,480 --> 01:18:20,959
My life.

618
01:18:21,800 --> 01:18:23,870
Let it be your life.

619
01:18:25,880 --> 01:18:26,995
Oh, Norman!

620
01:18:30,400 --> 01:18:33,790
What happened to you?.
- I slipped in the mud.

621
01:18:34,520 --> 01:18:36,033
I slipped too.

622
01:18:36,440 --> 01:18:39,159
I know I've hurt you.

623
01:18:39,560 --> 01:18:41,790
Can you forgive me?.
- Norman!

624
01:18:58,680 --> 01:19:00,830
Maureen?. Maureen?.

625
01:19:10,200 --> 01:19:12,794
Mother!

626
01:19:23,800 --> 01:19:25,119
Maureen?.

627
01:20:05,000 --> 01:20:07,468
Get that whore out of my house!

628
01:20:07,880 --> 01:20:11,475
Throw her down in the mud,
filth, where she belongs.

629
01:20:12,920 --> 01:20:16,230
I'll get you for this, Mother.
I'll get you for this.

630
01:20:17,000 --> 01:20:20,231
You haven't got the guts, boy.

631
01:22:14,080 --> 01:22:17,311
You dumb, stupid,

632
01:22:17,720 --> 01:22:20,280
naive girl.

633
01:22:28,200 --> 01:22:31,397
Why can't you leave my poor son,
my Norman, alone?.

634
01:22:41,320 --> 01:22:45,677
What set you off again, Norman?.
You killed Mrs. Spool, didn't you?.

635
01:22:47,720 --> 01:22:50,518
Did she tell you
that she was your mother?.

636
01:22:50,920 --> 01:22:53,832
She was crazy, Norman,
but she wasn't your mother.

637
01:22:54,240 --> 01:22:55,992
Neither are you!

638
01:22:58,000 --> 01:23:00,719
She was your aunt,
and in love with your father.

639
01:23:01,120 --> 01:23:04,749
But your mother stole him
away from her. Emma Spool...

640
01:23:05,160 --> 01:23:10,632
killed your father in a jealous rage
and kidnapped you as a baby.

641
01:23:15,000 --> 01:23:18,993
She killed your father
because she thought you were hers.

642
01:23:20,000 --> 01:23:22,798
The child
she should've had with him.

643
01:23:25,600 --> 01:23:26,999
She was crazy.

644
01:23:27,400 --> 01:23:31,996
They locked her away.
- It's lies, it's all lies.

645
01:23:33,200 --> 01:23:35,953
She's a lying whore.
- Norman, where are you?.

646
01:23:36,360 --> 01:23:38,157
She's a slut.

647
01:23:41,400 --> 01:23:44,517
Don't let her talk about me like that.

648
01:23:46,840 --> 01:23:48,398
Norman, please listen to me!

649
01:23:49,000 --> 01:23:54,836
Norman, Mrs. Bates! Whoever you are.
It doesn't matter to me.

650
01:23:55,240 --> 01:23:58,118
Get her, boy.
Get her, just like the others!

651
01:24:01,280 --> 01:24:04,590
Get her!
- No! No!

652
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:09,312
Don't! Don't! Please! Norman!

653
01:24:09,720 --> 01:24:10,709
No!

654
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:16,198
Norman, can't you do anything right?.

655
01:24:17,880 --> 01:24:22,556
